Around 9,200 Russian servicemen have lost their lives in the invasion of Ukraine, according to Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky. Russian authorities deny heavy losses, with state media claiming to have only lost 498. Meanwhile, a close ally of Putin, Belarusian leader Alexander Lukashenko, has announced the Belarusian armed forces will not take part in Russia's attack on Ukraine. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...